THE management of the Ministry of Information and Communications in Kogi State has been urged to comply with the requirements and policies of the Treasury Single Account (TSA) holistically. The Commissioner of Information and Communications, Kingsley Fanwo, gave charged during the management meeting he held with high ranking civil servants and heads of departments of the ministry in Lokoja on Monday. The commissioner said the compliance is in the best interest and for the well-being of the entire state, and also to block leakages in the income and expenditure of the state. Coronavirus: What Nigeria’s govt needs to do to… Mali President acknowledges contacts with jihadists Kogi govt to relocate beggars from major streets Powerful winter storm leaves at least five dead in Europe ALSO READ: JUST IN: Naira Marley’s twitter account hacked, Nigerians react While reiterating strict compliance, Fanwo added that it will enhance the manifestation of the blueprint of the ‘Let’s Do More’ peomises of Governor Yahaya Bello aimed at the rapid development Kogi State. “All payment of services to be rendered by parastatals and departments in the ministry must be paid into the purse of Kogi Internal Revenue Service (KGIRS),” Fanwo said. He also promised to interface with the KGIRS for easier working relationship and for the actualisation of their respective targets. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.